	ICRM doctors help infertile couples to&nbsp;become parents with the help of&nbsp;egg donation, embryo adoption and surrogacy programs. Our patients can suggest their own candidate to&nbsp;an&nbsp;egg donor and a&nbsp;surrogate mother, or&nbsp;select one from our bank.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Egg donation IVF program&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The program is&nbsp;offered to&nbsp;those patients who do&nbsp;not have their own oocytes (due to&nbsp;premature ovarian failure, removal of&nbsp;the ovaries in&nbsp;the history or&nbsp;menopause), who have too few eggs and for this reason good embryos cannot be&nbsp;made in&nbsp;IVF cycles, or&nbsp;if&nbsp;a&nbsp;woman has a&nbsp;hereditary disease. Here are the stages of&nbsp;the treatment program:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pre-treatment examination and tests for a&nbsp;recipient (a&nbsp;woman who has problems with oocytes) and an&nbsp;egg donor;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IVF/ICSI treatment program that includes hormonal stimulation of&nbsp;the donor’s ovaries and preparation of&nbsp;the recipient’s endometrium for embryo transfer;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fertilization of&nbsp;the donor’s eggs retrieved at&nbsp;the follicular puncture with the sperm of&nbsp;the recipient’s partner or&nbsp;donor in&nbsp;the laboratory;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;embryo culture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;embryo transfer to&nbsp;the prepared womb of&nbsp;the recipient;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;post-transfer support with medications;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pregnancy testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	If&nbsp;frozen donor eggs are used, some of&nbsp;the stages are skipped&nbsp;— donor eggs will just be&nbsp;thawed when necessary and fertilized, then the best embryos will be&nbsp;transferred to&nbsp;the recipient’s uterine cavity.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Embryo donation IVF treatment program&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In&nbsp;IVF protocols with the embryos made of&nbsp;donor eggs and donor sperm, both fresh and frozen biological material can be&nbsp;used (but only frozen donor sperm). If&nbsp;fresh oocytes are used, the following stages will be&nbsp;completed before the embryo transfer and pregnancy testing:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pre-treatment examination and tests for a&nbsp;recipient and a&nbsp;donor;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;eggs retrieval by&nbsp;means of&nbsp;hormonal stimulation of&nbsp;the donor’s ovaries and her follicle puncture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;donor eggs fertilization by&nbsp;donor sperm followed by&nbsp;embryo culture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;preparation of&nbsp;the recipient’s uterine lining.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In&nbsp;the case of&nbsp;frozen donor eggs, the protocol will be&nbsp;much shorter&nbsp;— it&nbsp;will only be&nbsp;necessary to&nbsp;prepare the endometrium of&nbsp;the future mother, to&nbsp;thaw the embryo when it&nbsp;is&nbsp;necessary and transfer it&nbsp;into her womb. In&nbsp;ICRM, we&nbsp;offer PGT-tested and recommended for transfer embryos for adoption.
&lt;/p&gt;";}s:11:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'original";a:20:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"186";s:4:"NAME";s:9:"Donorship";s:4:"CODE";s:23:"donorship-and-surrogacy";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2834";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:53:"IVF with donor eggs or sperm. Our own bank of donors.";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:34:"/services/donorship-and-surrogacy/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"20";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:5:"menu-";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"1";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:3031:"&lt;p&gt;
